  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: In the absence of further details, the proposed rear facing flue/plant would, by reason of its positioning and height, represent a visually incongrous addition which is harmful to the character and appearance of the Highbury Fields Conservation Area. The proposed flue would fail to discharge at a height of 1m above the eaves of the existing building unacceptably allowing odours and gases to discharge at a height where they would cause harm to the ongoing amenity and health of occupiers of the upper floor residential unit contrary to policies D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (2021), policies PLAN1, DH1 and DH2 of Islington’s Strategic and Development Management Policies (2023), and the guidance contained within the Urban Design Guide (2017) and the Highbury Fields Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002)."
